    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen using Neovim nightly there is a bug with `nvim_buf_set_lines` when the buffer is not the active one. After calling this function, the buffer is scrolled to top, not preserving the current cursor position. When I switch to the buffer with changed lines, the cursor position is restored and the window is scrolled correctly. It works as expected in Neovim 0.9.5.\r\n\r\nNightly:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3128467/b4b0b65a-50cd-413e-8663-53638c721679\r\n\r\n0.9.5:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3128467/b73476c4-a3d7-4a3b-85db-636823847553\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal lines = {}\r\nfor i = 1, 100 do\r\n  lines[i] = tostring(i)\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(OTHER_BUFFER_ID, 0, -1, false, lines)\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Run Neovim nightly\r\n2. Run the provided script for your buffer (use `:luafile` for example)\r\n3. Set your cursor position somewhere in the middle of the file.\r\n4. Create a split and run the provided script for the previously configured buffer (make sure to set the correct buffer id, it can't be 0).\r\n\r\nResult: the buffer is scrolled to top.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe updated buffer should preserve it's cursor position without scrolling to top.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-2501+gdbf6be296\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.2.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niTerm2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nscreen-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nrepo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Workaround:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nfor i, line in ipairs(lines) do\r\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(M.bufnr, i - 1, i, false, { line })\r\nend\r\n```",
