            "body": "Here is the code to reproduce it... the buffer with the content is scrolled to top after setting lines. When you focus it again, the expected scroll position is restored.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal lines = {}\r\nfor i = 1, 100 do\r\n  lines[i] = tostring(i)\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.cmd(\":new\")\r\nlocal newBuf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(newBuf, 0, -1, false, lines)\r\nvim.cmd(\":50\")\r\n\r\nvim.cmd(\"vnew\")\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(newBuf, 0, -1, false, lines)\r\n```",
